context: The George Brown College offers various programs in the field of Health and Wellness. These programs aim to improve daily life for people by providing services such as making leg braces and artificial limbs, testing hearing and dispensing hearing aids, designing physical programs for the elderly, and working with those diagnosed with autism spectrum disorder. The college provides an Entry Advising service for free to help match skills, background, and career goals with program options.
